    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Improve in-process LSP server for confirmation buffer with the following code lenses/actions:\n\n- \"Update this plugin\": update plugin-at-cursor. Useful if there are only handful of plugins user want to update.\n\n- \"Skip updating this plugin\": skip update plugin-at-cursor. Useful if there are only handful of plugins user wants to skip.\n\n- \"Delete this plugin\": deletes this plugin from disk.\n\nExecuting any of the above actions will remove target plugin from current confirmation report: executing `:write` will do nothing with the plugin (as there was already an action done for it).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Very low-priority imo. This is the kind of thing that third-party plugins can offer by extending/wrapping `vim.pack`. I don't get why someone is calling `vim.pack.add()` and then wants to skip updates (they can pin the `version`). Maybe I'm out of touch though, let's see how many upvotes this gets.",
